===Introductions by Brust===
* In 1987, Tor Books published the gamebook &quot;Dzurlord (A Crossroads Adventure in the World of Steven Brust&#x27;s Jhereg)&quot;. Brust wrote the introduction for this book, which introduced readers to the world of Dragaera and its inhabitants.
* Tor also published &quot;The Three Musketeers&quot; in paperback in 1994. Brust introduced the edition, saying that this translation (anonymous, originally published in 1888) was his favorite.
* Brust contributed the introduction for &quot;Manna from Heaven&quot;. Wildside Press published this collection of stories from Roger Zelazny in 2003.

== Trivia ==
=== References in other media ===
* Brust&#x27;s book &quot;Dragon&quot; is the subject of an argument in the webcomic &quot;Penny Arcade&quot;. Cartoonist Jerry Holkins later noted that the comic was based on an actual conversation about Brust&#x27;s work at a convention.
* Brust&#x27;s band, Cats Laughing, appears in issue no. 5 of the Marvel comic book &quot;Excalibur&quot;. Brust is the only member of the band who is both seen onstage and named. Emma Bull also appears, but names everyone in the band except herself. Brust was seen again in a one-shot special issue, &quot;Excalibur: Mojo Mayhem&quot;, in which the mutant superhero Shadowcat attends a Cats Laughing concert in Edinburgh and mentions previously having seen the band at Windycon.

=== Book title nicknames ===
Brust is known for his propensity to give his books alternate titles for his own amusement. These have cropped up in numerous interviews and online forums, starting with &quot;Jarhead&quot; for &quot;Jhereg&quot;. Examples include:

* Jarhead (&quot;Jhereg&quot;)
* The Rain in Spain (&quot;To Reign in Hell&quot;)
* Yentl (&quot;Yendi&quot;)
* Ripple (&quot;Brokedown Palace&quot;)
* Tacky (&quot;Teckla&quot;)
* Crosby, Stills, and Nash (&quot;The Sun, the Moon, and the Stars&quot;)
* Milquetoast (&quot;Taltos&quot;)
* Shit Happens (&quot;Cowboy Feng&#x27;s Space Bar and Grille&quot;)
* Tucson (&quot;Phoenix&quot;)
* The Kleenex Guards (&quot;The Phoenix Guards&quot;)
* Aw, Gee (&quot;Agyar&quot;)
* Urethra (&quot;Athyra&quot;)
* Five Hundred Beers After (&quot;Five Hundred Years After&quot;)
* Porker (&quot;Orca&quot;)
* Drag Queen (&quot;Dragon&quot;)
* Is Ole (&quot;Issola&quot;)
* The Laughs of the Fred (&quot;The Paths of the Dead&quot;)
* The Whore of Castle Smack (&quot;The Lord of Castle Black&quot;)
* Send in the Toad (&quot;Sethra Lavode&quot;)
* Stir (&quot;Dzur&quot;)
* Gigolo (&quot;Jhegaala&quot;)
* My Own Kind of Whedon (&quot;My Own Kind of Freedom&quot;, &quot;Firefly&quot; fanfic)
* Your Itch (&quot;Iorich&quot;)
* Three Asses/Hadassah (&quot;Tiassa&quot;)
* Spit (&quot;Hawk&quot;)
* Good Goys (&quot;Good Guys&quot;)
* Barista (&quot;Vallista&quot;)
* Tall Mouth (&quot;Tsalmoth&quot;)

Brust does not have nicknames for collaborations out of respect for his collaborators, stating &quot;It&#x27;s one thing to not want to take myself seriously, and another thing to—I want to take them seriously.&quot;

